# u-oos-really-basic-folder-security

A single PHP file that acts as a gate and prevents the user from accessing the directory listing without a password.

It also gives the user a log in window that can be used to access the first .html (or .htm) file in the folder.

This allows giving the user only the address of the folder, and limit access with a password.

## Links

- **Git**: <git@ec2-54-232-93-180.sa-east-1.compute.amazonaws.com:emailsfrontend-team/u-oos-really-basic-folder-security.git>


## Installation

Just copy the content of example folder to a new protected folder. The file ".password" is optional.

### Folder structure

    \protected_folder
     |--- index.php
     |--- protected_file.html
     \--- .password (optional)
	 
#### IMPORTANT

You must change the name of the protected file to something hard to guess.

Try append a timestamp at the end of the file name:
	
	Ex: protected_file.html  --> protected_file_1489671236.html
	
## How to use

### Password

The default password is: _"guest"_.

You may change it in two ways:

1. Change the variable **$default_pwd** on line 18 in **index.php** to any password you like:

		$default_pwd = "guest"; //Default password

2. Create a file named **".password"** (please take notice of the leading dot) inside the protected folder, and append the password as a plain text string. This password
will be used in this folder instead of the default.

>**NOTE**: If you are using Windows OS and don't know how to create a new text file with a leading dot in the filename, try copy and edit the one in the **\dist** folder, or try to create the file directly in the web server through the FTP program.

### Logout

You can logout from the current folder adding "[?logout](?logout)" to the URL.


## Requirements

A web server with PHP 5+.
